  "body": "### Description\n\nHibernate 6 has an integration with `ObjectMapper` to write map an object to JSON directly.\r\n\r\nCurrently it is possible to specifiy our own ObjectMapper using a custom FormatMapper implementation using the key `hibernate.type.json_format_mapper`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/hibernate/hibernate-orm/blob/main/hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/type/format/jackson/JacksonIntegration.java\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if Quarkus provided an automatic way to provide the configured ObjectMapper.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
